NODE RETENTION REFERENCE
========================
Which C++ node types actually survive into the final AST, and which get absorbed.

HOW passAlong WORKS
-------------------
passAlong(nodeType, newnode) does:
  1. Pops the top of the semantic stack (the "source" node)
  2. Copies ALL fields from source into newnode via copyNode()
  3. Transfers source's children to newnode via adoptChildren()
  4. Deletes the source node (its memory is freed)
  5. Pushes newnode onto the semantic stack (or sets it as tree root if nodeType=="start")

The KEY effect: the C++ runtime type CHANGES. If #classdecl pushed a classdeclNode,
then #class does passAlong which pops it, copies data into a classNode, and deletes the
classdeclNode. The tree now has a classNode whose semanticMeaning is still "classdecl".

This means: visitor dispatch goes to visit(classNode&), NOT visit(classdeclNode&).


========================================================================
PASSALONG NODES — these are the ACTUAL C++ types in the final AST
========================================================================
Semantic Action   C++ Type Created     Absorbs Top-of-Stack    semanticMeaning
---------------   ------------------   ---------------------   ---------------
#start            startNode            (whatever is on top)    "start"
#aparamstail      aparamstailNode      top node                from source
#arithexpr        arithexprNode        top node                from source
#arraysize        arraysizeNode        top node                from source
#attributedecl    attributedeclNode    top node                from source
#class            classNode            classdeclNode           "classdecl"
#impl             implNode             impldefNode             "impldef"
#func             funcNode             funcdefNode             "funcdef"
#factor           factorNode           top node                from source
#idnest2          idnest2Node          top node                from source
#funcbody         funcbodyNode         reptfuncbody1Node       from source
#funcdecl         funcdeclNode         top node                from source
#indice           indiceNode           top node                from source
#localvardecl     localvardeclNode     top node                from source
#localvardeclorstat localvardeclorstatNode top node            from source
#prog             progNode             reptprog0Node           from source
#condition        conditionNode        top node                from source
#then             thenNode             top node                from source
#felse            felseNode            top node                from source
#statblock        statblockNode        reptstatblock1Node      from source
#returntype       returntypeNode       top node                "returntype"
#term             termNode             top node                from source

Visitor override needed:   visit(classNode&), visit(implNode&), visit(funcNode&), etc.
Visitor override DEAD:     visit(classdeclNode&), visit(impldefNode&), visit(funcdefNode&), etc.


