BINARY SUBTREE NODES (makeBinarySubTree / makeBinarySubTreeWithHead)
========================================================================
These pop 2-4 nodes and wire them as a binary structure. They always SURVIVE.

Semantic Action        C++ Type Created
---------------        -------------------
#dot                   dotNode                (pops 2, mode 0)
#rightrecarithexpr     rightrecarithexprNode  (pops 3, mode 1: middle promoted)
#rightrecterm          rightrectermNode        (pops 3, mode 1: middle promoted)
#reptstatement4        reptstatement4Node     (pops 3, mode 1: middle promoted)
#whilestatement        whilestatementNode     (pops 3 with head)
#readstatement         readstatementNode      (pops 2 with head)
#writestatement        writestatementNode     (pops 2 with head)
#freturnstatement      freturnstatementNode   (pops 2 with head)
#ifstatement           ifstatementNode        (pops 4 with head)


========================================================================
ABSORPTION CHAINS — full sequence for key constructs
========================================================================

Class declaration:
  #p → epsilonNode (sentinel)
  ... member decls pushed ...
  #reptclassdecl4 → reptclassdecl4Node (makeSubTree, pops to epsilon)
  #classdecl → classdeclNode (makeSubTree, pops 3: id, optclassdecl2, reptclassdecl4)
  #class → classNode (passAlong, ABSORBS classdeclNode → classNode with semanticMeaning="classdecl")

Implementation:
  #impldef → impldefNode (makeSubTree, pops 2: funchead, reptimpldef3)
  #impl → implNode (passAlong, ABSORBS impldefNode → implNode with semanticMeaning="impldef")

Function definition:
  #funcdef → funcdefNode (makeSubTree, pops 2: funchead, funcbody)
  #func → funcNode (passAlong, ABSORBS funcdefNode → funcNode with semanticMeaning="funcdef")

Program:
  #reptprog0 → reptprog0Node (makeSubTree, pops to epsilon)
  #prog → progNode (passAlong, ABSORBS reptprog0Node)
  #start → startNode (passAlong, ABSORBS progNode, becomes AST root)


========================================================================
VISITOR DISPATCH SUMMARY
========================================================================
When implementing a visitor, use these C++ types (the actual runtime types):

  For class declarations:    visit(classNode&)      NOT visit(classdeclNode&)
  For implementations:       visit(implNode&)       NOT visit(impldefNode&)
  For function definitions:  visit(funcNode&)       NOT visit(funcdefNode&)
  For function bodies:       visit(funcbodyNode&)   NOT visit(reptfuncbody1Node&)
  For program root:          visit(progNode&)       NOT visit(reptprog0Node&)
  For stat blocks:           visit(statblockNode&)  NOT visit(reptstatblock1Node&)
  For tree root:             visit(startNode&)

The semanticMeaning field preserves the original label (e.g. "classdecl", "impldef"),
but the C++ type (and therefore virtual dispatch) uses the absorbing type.